Package edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.util

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Queue<E>
    Interface class which is to be used by LinkedQueue or ArrayQueue.
    Stack<E>
    Abstract interface for Stack type collections, in which elements can only be accessed if they are "on top." Also includes field related methods as well as accessors.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayList<E>
    This is the ArraysList class which extends the AbstractList
    ArrayQueue<E>
    ArrayList that uses the Queue interface
    ArrayQueueTest
    Test class which is used against the ArrayQueue class
    ArrayStack<E>
    Stack type class created by imposing limitations on an ArrayList field so that values can only be accessed from the most recent additions.
    ArrayStackTest
    This class tests the methods of the ArrayStack class, initializing an instance of said class before each test run to ensure test integrity
    LinkedAbstractList<E>
    The LinkedAbstractList uses a Linked List of ListNodes to implement a list.
    LinkedList<E>
    The LinkedList uses a Linked List of ListNodes to implement a list.
    LinkedListRecursive<E>
    Represents a recursive collection of data using the linked list paradigm.
    LinkedListTest
    Tester class to test the LinkedList class
    LinkedQueue<E>
    LinkedAbstractList that uses the Queue interface
    LinkedQueueTest
    Test class to be put against LinkedQueue
    LinkedStack<E>
    Stack type class created by imposing limitations on an LinkedAbstractList field so that values can only be accessed from the most recent additions.
    LinkedStackTest
    This class tests the methods of the LinkedStack class, initializing an instance of said class before each test run to ensure test integrity
